@startuml
title Books Store Application - Control Flow Sequence Diagram

actor User
participant "Blazor WebAssembly\n(Books.Web)" as Blazor
participant "Auth0" as Auth0
participant "Azure API\nManagement" as APIM
participant "BooksController\n(Books.APIV1)" as Controller
participant "BooksBll\n(Business Logic)" as BLL
participant "BookCacheRepository\n(Redis Cache)" as Cache
participant "BookRepository\n(SQL DAL)" as Repository
database "Redis Cache" as Redis
database "SQL Server\n(BooksDataStore)" as DB

== User Authentication ==
User -> Blazor: Access Application
Blazor -> Auth0: Request Authentication
Auth0 -> Auth0: Validate Credentials
Auth0 --> Blazor: Return Auth Token
Blazor --> User: Display UI

== Get Books (Cache Hit) ==
User -> Blazor: Request Book List
Blazor -> APIM: GET /api/books\n(with Auth Token)
APIM -> APIM: Validate Token & Route
APIM -> Controller: GET /books
activate Controller
Controller -> BLL: GetAllBooksAsync()
activate BLL
BLL -> Cache: GetAllBooksAsync()
activate Cache
Cache -> Redis: Get Books from Cache
Redis --> Cache: Return Cached Data
Cache --> BLL: Return Books
deactivate Cache
BLL --> Controller: Return Books
deactivate BLL
Controller --> APIM: 200 OK (Books Data)
deactivate Controller
APIM --> Blazor: Books JSON
Blazor --> User: Display Books

== Get Books (Cache Miss) ==
User -> Blazor: Request Book List
Blazor -> APIM: GET /api/books
APIM -> Controller: GET /books
activate Controller
Controller -> BLL: GetAllBooksAsync()
activate BLL
BLL -> Cache: GetAllBooksAsync()
activate Cache
Cache -> Redis: Get Books from Cache
Redis --> Cache: Cache Miss (null)
Cache --> BLL: Return null
deactivate Cache
BLL -> Repository: GetAllBooksAsync()
activate Repository
Repository -> DB: SELECT * FROM Books
DB --> Repository: Return Book Records
Repository --> BLL: Return Books
deactivate Repository
BLL -> Cache: SetAsync(Books)
activate Cache
Cache -> Redis: Store Books in Cache
Redis --> Cache: Success
Cache --> BLL: Cached
deactivate Cache
BLL --> Controller: Return Books
deactivate BLL
Controller --> APIM: 200 OK (Books Data)
deactivate Controller
APIM --> Blazor: Books JSON
Blazor --> User: Display Books

== Add New Book ==
User -> Blazor: Submit New Book Form
Blazor -> APIM: POST /api/books\n(Book Data)
APIM -> Controller: POST /books
activate Controller
Controller -> BLL: AddBookAsync(Book)
activate BLL
BLL -> Repository: AddBookAsync(Book)
activate Repository
Repository -> DB: INSERT INTO Books
DB --> Repository: Book Created
Repository --> BLL: Return New Book
deactivate Repository
BLL -> Cache: InvalidateCacheAsync()
activate Cache
Cache -> Redis: Delete Books Cache
Redis --> Cache: Cache Cleared
Cache --> BLL: Success
deactivate Cache
BLL --> Controller: Return New Book
deactivate BLL
Controller --> APIM: 201 Created (Book)
deactivate Controller
APIM --> Blazor: Success Response
Blazor --> User: Display Success Message

== Update Book ==
User -> Blazor: Submit Edit Book Form
Blazor -> APIM: PUT /api/books/{id}
APIM -> Controller: PUT /books/{id}
activate Controller
Controller -> BLL: UpdateBookAsync(Book)
activate BLL
BLL -> Repository: UpdateBookAsync(Book)
activate Repository
Repository -> DB: UPDATE Books SET ...
DB --> Repository: Book Updated
Repository --> BLL: Return Updated Book
deactivate Repository
BLL -> Cache: InvalidateCacheAsync()
activate Cache
Cache -> Redis: Delete Books Cache
Redis --> Cache: Cache Cleared
Cache --> BLL: Success
deactivate Cache
BLL --> Controller: Return Updated Book
deactivate BLL
Controller --> APIM: 200 OK (Book)
deactivate Controller
APIM --> Blazor: Success Response
Blazor --> User: Display Updated Book

== Delete Book ==
User -> Blazor: Click Delete Book
Blazor -> APIM: DELETE /api/books/{id}
APIM -> Controller: DELETE /books/{id}
activate Controller
Controller -> BLL: DeleteBookAsync(id)
activate BLL
BLL -> Repository: DeleteBookAsync(id)
activate Repository
Repository -> DB: DELETE FROM Books WHERE Id = id
DB --> Repository: Book Deleted
Repository --> BLL: Success
deactivate Repository
BLL -> Cache: InvalidateCacheAsync()
activate Cache
Cache -> Redis: Delete Books Cache
Redis --> Cache: Cache Cleared
Cache --> BLL: Success
deactivate Cache
BLL --> Controller: Success
deactivate BLL
Controller --> APIM: 204 No Content
deactivate Controller
APIM --> Blazor: Success Response
Blazor --> User: Remove Book from UI

@enduml
